```latex
\documentclass{standalone}
\usepackage{tikz}

\begin{document}

\begin{tikzpicture}[scale=2]

% Define the coordinates for T_i, T_{i+1}, and the center of the arc C_i
\coordinate (T_i) at (0, 0);
\coordinate (T_ip1) at (3, 0);
\coordinate (C_i_center) at (1.5, 1);

% Draw the dotted segments T_i to T_{i+1} and T_{i+1} to T_i (reversed)
\draw[dotted] (T_i) -- node[midway, below] {$\widetilde{T}_i$} (T_ip1);
\draw[dotted] (T_ip1) -- node[midway, above] {$\widetilde{T}_{i+1}$} (T_i);

% Calculate the length of each dotted segment
\pgfmathsetmacro{\segmentLength}{a_{n+1}/100}

% Draw the arc C_i joining T_i and T_{i+1}
\draw[thick] (C_i_center) .. controls +(45:0.5) and +(-45:0.5) .. node[midway, above right] {$C_i$} (T_i |- C_i_center) to[out=-45,in=45] (T_ip1 |- C_i_center) .. controls +(-45:0.5) and +(45:0.5) .. (T_ip1);

% Label the length of the dotted segments
\node at ($(T_i)!0.5!(T_ip1)$) [below] {\tiny $\frac{a_{n+1}}{100}$};
\node at ($(T_ip1)!0.5!(T_i)$) [above] {\tiny $\frac{a_{n+1}}{100}$};

\end{tikzpicture}

\end{document}
```

### Explanation:
- **Coordinates**: `T_i` and `T_{i+1}` are defined at `(0, 0)` and `(3, 0)` respectively.
- **Arc Center**: `C_i_center` is positioned at `(1.5, 1)`.

